  "title": "Invocations during Ruki' (bowing in prayer)",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 36",
  "arabic": "اللَّهُمَّ لَكَ رَكَعْتُ وَبِكَ آمَنْتُ وَلَكَ أَسْلَمْتُ خَشَعَ لَكَ سَمْعِي وَبَصَرِي وَمُخِّي وَعَظْمِي وَعَصَبِي وَمَا استَقَلَّتْ بِهِ قَدَمِي",
  "meaning": "O Allah, unto You I have bowed, and in You I have believed, and to You I have submitted. My hearing, sight, mind, bones, tendons and what my feet carry are humbled before You.",
